Zapatero and the red line Germany
Berlin has opted for keeping the euro, but at the same time, conditions for the whole of the European Union.
The tensions in the markets have a dual response from the government.
On the one hand, José Luis Rodríguez Zapatero has submitted new adaptation measures, starting with tax reliefs for small and micro-enterprises, regulating temporary work agencies or the lifting of the 426 euro support for the unemployed, no unemployment benefit related to the privatisation of 49% of AENA, the management of airports Barajas and El Prat and 30% of the state lottery.
On the other hand, supports the deputy leader, Elena Salgado, with the help of the former Prime Minister Felipe González, the criticism of the Chancellor Angela Merkel as responsible for the current crisis presents.
How are these transactions to understand?
It is anticipated that Merkel's position is not a mistake of their public relations.
On the contrary, it is a new round in the difficult process of redefining the euro.
It is Germany a fundamentally new perspective to shape our future to maintain ancient traditions clash of much of its partners.
Given the resistance in Europe begins one in Germany to spekuliern on three possible ways out of the crisis.
The first: A strong euro Germany, Austria, the Netherlands and other countries, while the south to leave the euro area.
The Second: The reintroduction of the Deutsche Mark - although it is more science fiction sounds - supported by a large part of public opinion, approximately 50% of the population.
The Third: A transformation of the euro under German proposals. This means: More macroeconomic control; strict budgetary management; penalise the countries, broken; möglichereweise the default of certain countries, and the extension of the costs of potential adjustment measures on the private sector.
The German position is clear and has been for some time. So there are no excuses now.
First 2009, as both the IMF and the European Commission for deficits, and the German Government constitutional reform, in order to prevent it from 2016.
It was the first signs of the polarisation between what Germany was thought necessary (strict fiscal plans and stable public finances) and the practices of its European partners, including France.
The second sign the Central European country than Merkel postponed the decision to save Greece painful,.
Then it was strongly criticised. But the fact is that the political consensus in Germany, the public and the published absolutely against a rescue of Greece.
Finally, Merkel in the last October days again with a clear position, It calls for a reform of the European Union agreements, to enable the rescue of one country while private lenders to commit a part of the cost.
This position was interpreted as anti-European, since they propelled Ireland crisis and everything.
But her proposal, if a little sweetened, was approved in the coming months we will participate in the reform of the European Union, which these measures from 2013.
Germany has drawn a red line that it intends not to exceed.
It says all that - even if unpopular measures must be taken, from that date there will no longer be the old ways of the euro.
2013 will be the birth of a new currency area, in which the countries to ban be severely punished, be forced to declare themselves bankrupt and in this case, the private sector must play a part of the cost.
Germany shows us that we need a strong growth path, with high savings and investment rates, moderation of consumption, improving productivity and competitiveness and positive external balances.
The alternative, which is based on debt and construction with huge holes in the balance of payments, as was mentioned by Spain in boom times, will simply not be tolerated.
The offer is clear.
And we would badly do not understand it.
It is not just about the deficit to 3% by the year 2013 runterzufahren.
The demands are much harder.
Under these conditions, And the worst thing we could do is to cheat.
I hope that the current turbulence in more calm.
And that we will use the opportunities offered to us by early 2013.
It seems that Zapatero has taken this so well, and his double announcement (the promised reforms after the meeting with the large companies last Saturday and the announcement of new measures yesterday) suggests that, despite the criticism of Merkel hypothesis, in order to make their way.
But Germany-red line is there, and it is not that something would change.
Among the possibilities is that In countries with little serious full gestopften euro area, not to be excluded.
In this case, we still say it could have warned us.
Sport and usually bypass
Tricks as Alonso and Ramos in the match against Ajax show inventiveness, but not the desire to bypass a sanction.
The supposedly from two players of Real Madrid (Xabi Alonso and Sergio Ramos) has instigated exclusion in the game on 23 November against Ajax in the Champions League led to much ink has been shed about, whether it was a unsportliche act or not and whether both players should be sanctioned by UEFA.
As is well known, lost two players a few minutes before game end (their team had already clearly won) time and played several fouls, now the second yellow card by referee showed.
In this way, and since the Real Madrid his group, the two players would meet the prescribed sanction the next league game against Auxerre and without maps in the next game phase.
Finally, the Disziplinarkommitee of UEFA, the coach of the club, José Mourinho, with two games and the players involved with different sums of money.
The provocation of a yellow card in this or similar circumstances is not a new practice, it is more often in the world of football.
It is so widespread that it is part of the ethos - the unwritten but followed in the sport's rules.
Part of the debate that have arisen outlined the case goes back to that a team of football clubs, Real Madrid (his anthem Edelmut claims and honour and on other occasions his players for similar incidents had punished) played the key role, and the drama by Mourinho, the episode has added to its long history, more than theatralischer and provocative technicians.
In any case, the debate about whether this is not explicitly prohibited by the statutes behaviour contradicts the principles of the sport, that is, whether these actions constitute a rule circumvention. indeed, this approach to the statutes of the sport, but its meaning.
The damage caused to the sporting spirit should be examined in this matter.
The sporting spirit defended the physical integrity of the opponent, an aspect that was not compromised by these actions, because there was no aggressive game.
Another aspect of a clean game is to avoid that to ban players an unjustified. Also benefits from the team that has not been done.
The paradox of the action of Real Madrid's players is that they do not correspond to what we normally under wrong game or rule bypass understand, because the circumvention of the rule has not been secretly, in order to avoid a penalty, but it should be as conspicuous as possible, so that they will be punished by the referee.
The players waited and took the sanction happily.
Another question is what kind of advantage the offender from the deliberate fouls.
It should be emphasised that the rival either in a disadvantageous position was still benefits for the feigned game were erheischt because the obvious result of this action was that the team with fewer players had to play.
It is also not a useful strategy for the next game, because then the club does not have these players.
Obviously The advantage is that the players the next phase of the Champions League game without tickets, their participation in a future game could begin.
But it is a long-term, up to a certain point uncertain advantage because the team could eventually retire. With this approach, players also receive a sanction and go in the second cycle on cards, because card accumulation with a card less than in the first cycle of departures.
So it is not clear whether it is really an advantage.
Ultimately, such practices are not directed against the sporting spirit, also include strategic decisions from the rules a maximum benefit.
In this case the players wanted to avoid any penalty (that would actually be a clear case of rule bypass), they wanted more when they undergo this.
They took a strategic decision, without a sentence or to flee before her.
Although the border between imagination and Regelumgebung is, I believe, that this is a clear case of inventiveness.
I have the impression that the controversy has arisen as a result of two factors: Because two exclusions and because of the way the provoking Regelübertragung.
The damage done to the principles of the sport by these acts is less ethical than aesthetic.
