In particular, the nature of the Pakistani nuclear programme - that the weapons are made up, but its individual parts are stored in a possible attack their destruction - Washington sleepless nights.
These risks include the ambassador in Pakistan, Anne W. Patterson, in a report before the visit by the former head of the National Security Council, James Jones, said: "The proximity of some nuclear plants by the Taliban ravaged area, the probable were scattered of nuclear material and the vulnerability of transport of nuclear material."
